\begin{align*}
3n &= 135 \\
n &= 45
\end{align*}
Now, substituting the value of $n$ back into the first equation, we get:
\begin{align*}
f + 2(45) &= 155 \\
f + 90 &= 155 \\
f &= 65
\end{align*}
So, the flat fee for the first night is $\boxed{\$65}$.

